sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_classrooms, AVG(capacity) AS average_capacity
FROM classrooms
WHERE building = 'Science Wing';

SELECT first_name, last_name, COUNT(*) AS teacher_count
FROM teachers
GROUP BY first_name, last_name;

external_knowledge:
- Cumulative utilization refers to the total utilization percentage over time slots;
- Average utilization is the mean utilization percentage calculated over all time slots per room;
- Teachers are associated with their subjects and the classrooms where they teach;
- Time slots are considered in the order they occur on a given date.

sql:
SELECT AVG(student_count) AS average_students_per_classroom
FROM (
    SELECT room_id, COUNT(*) AS student_count
    FROM subject_distribution
    GROUP BY room_id
) AS classroom_student_counts;
